49// Public for testing.
50// Inputs StreamStats for all types of substreams (kMedia, kRtx, kFlexfec) and
51// merges any non-kMedia substream stats object into its referenced kMedia-type
52// substream. The resulting substreams are all kMedia. This means, for example,
53// that packet and byte counters of RTX and FlexFEC streams are accounted for in
54// the relevant RTP media stream's stats. This makes the resulting StreamStats
55// objects ready to be turned into "outbound-rtp" stats objects for GetStats()
56// which does not create separate stream stats objects for complementary
57// streams.
58std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats>
59MergeInfoAboutOutboundRtpSubstreamsForTesting(
60 const std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats>& substreams);
61

573 // Using primary-ssrc (first ssrc) as key.
574 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoSendStream*> send_streams_
575 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
576 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoReceiveStream*> receive_streams_
577 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
578 // When the channel and demuxer get reconfigured, there is a window of time
579 // where we have to be prepared for packets arriving based on the old demuxer
580 // criteria because the streams live on the worker thread and the demuxer
581 // lives on the network thread. Because packets are posted from the network
582 // thread to the worker thread, they can still be in-flight when streams are
583 // reconfgured. This can happen when |demuxer_criteria_id_| and
584 // |demuxer_criteria_completed_id_| don't match. During this time, we do not
585 // want to create unsignalled receive streams and should instead drop the
586 // packets. E.g:
587 // * If RemoveRecvStream(old_ssrc) was recently called, there may be packets
588 // in-flight for that ssrc. This happens when a receiver becomes inactive.
589 // * If we go from one to many m= sections, the demuxer may change from
590 // forwarding all packets to only forwarding the configured ssrcs, so there
591 // is a risk of receiving ssrcs for other, recently added m= sections.
592 uint32_t demuxer_criteria_id_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_) = 0;
593 uint32_t demuxer_criteria_completed_id_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_) = 0;
594 std::set<uint32_t> send_ssrcs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
595 std::set<uint32_t> receive_ssrcs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
596
597 absl::optional<VideoCodecSettings> send_codec_
598 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
599 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> negotiated_codecs_
600 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
601
602 absl::optional<std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>> send_rtp_extensions_
603 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
604
605 webrtc::VideoEncoderFactory* const encoder_factory_
606 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
607 webrtc::VideoDecoderFactory* const decoder_factory_
608 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
609 webrtc::VideoBitrateAllocatorFactory* const bitrate_allocator_factory_
610 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
611 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> recv_codecs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
612 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> recv_rtp_extensions_
613 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
614 // See reason for keeping track of the FlexFEC payload type separately in
615 // comment in WebRtcVideoChannel::ChangedRecvParameters.
616 int recv_flexfec_payload_type_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
617 webrtc::BitrateConstraints bitrate_config_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
618 // TODO(deadbeef): Don't duplicate information between
619 // send_params/recv_params, rtp_extensions, options, etc.
620 VideoSendParameters send_params_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
621 VideoOptions default_send_options_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
622 VideoRecvParameters recv_params_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
623 int64_t last_stats_log_ms_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
624 const bool discard_unknown_ssrc_packets_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
625 // This is a stream param that comes from the remote description, but wasn't
626 // signaled with any a=ssrc lines. It holds information that was signaled
627 // before the unsignaled receive stream is created when the first packet is
628 // received.
629 StreamParams unsignaled_stream_params_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
630 // Per peer connection crypto options that last for the lifetime of the peer
631 // connection.
632 const webrtc::CryptoOptions crypto_options_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
633
634 // Optional frame transformer set on unsignaled streams.
635 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface>
636 unsignaled_frame_transformer_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
637
638 // Buffer for unhandled packets.
639 std::unique_ptr<UnhandledPacketsBuffer> unknown_ssrc_packet_buffer_
640 RTC_GUARDED_BY(thread_checker_);
641
642 bool allow_codec_switching_ = false;
643 absl::optional<EncoderSwitchRequestCallback::Config>
644 requested_encoder_switch_;
645};
